        "faq_1": {
          "type": "mini_faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes the retinol in this formula different?",
            "answer": "It uses microencapsulated retinol, designed for controlled release to support skin renewal while helping minimise irritation and barrier disruption."
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "mini_faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it irritate or thin my skin like other retinols?",
            "answer": "No—when used correctly within a protocol, it is designed to minimise irritation, not cause it.\n\nUltimate A uses microencapsulated retinol, which delivers the active gradually rather than all at once. This controlled release helps reduce common side effects such as redness, dryness, and barrier disruption.\n\nRetinol does not thin the skin. In fact, with consistent use it supports epidermal renewal and dermal collagen production, contributing to thicker, more resilient skin over time.\n\nSome initial adjustment (mild dryness or flaking) can occur, particularly if introduced too quickly. This is managed by:\n\nstarting 2–3 nights per week\nensuring adequate hydration and barrier support\navoiding concurrent strong exfoliation\n\nPrescribed correctly, the outcome is improved skin function—not compromise."
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "mini_faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What if it doesn’t work for me?",
            "answer": "We stand behind every bottle. If you’re not satisfied within 90 days, contact us for a full refund. No forms, no hassle."
          }
        }
      },
